# Rust Standards

- Use `thiserror` for all custom error types
- Never use `unwrap()` or `expect()` in production code; use `?` operator or explicit error handling
- Run `cargo clippy -- -D warnings` before committing
- Run `cargo fmt` before committing
- Use `#[cfg(test)]` modules for unit tests within each file
- Use `#[cfg(target_os = "windows")]` for Windows-specific code with trait-based abstractions for cross-platform testing
- Prefer `once_cell::sync::Lazy` or `std::sync::OnceLock` over `lazy_static`
- All public functions must have doc comments
- Error types must implement `Display` and `std::error::Error`
